<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="rude-adj">rude <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ruːd/    美 /ruːd/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-impolite">1.★ <strong>无礼的；粗鲁的 (impolite)</strong></h4>
<p>反 polite： </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>rude remarks / treatment 
粗鲁的话/粗暴的对待</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>in a rude manner 
以一种粗鲁的方式</p></div>

<ul>
<li>it is rude (of sb) to do sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>In some European countries it is rude to arrive late for dinner. 
在一些欧洲国家，出席宴会迟到是不礼貌的。</p><footer>外研⑧ – 3</footer></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="be-rude-to-sb">be rude to sb</h3>
<p>1.<strong>对某人无礼：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>You mustn’t be rude to teachers.
不能对老师无礼。</p><footer>外研④ – 7</footer></div>

<h2 id="_3">派生词汇</h2>
<p>rudely /'ruːdli/ adv   </p></div>